ATORY","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":16,"place_id":"dun-chaoin-dunquin-county-kerry-ireland","lon":-10.4631585,"lat":52.1242458,"place":"Dún Chaoin (Dunquin), County Kerry, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"main_stop","quote":"The drystone walls are covered in grass. Red & purple fuschias, blue, yellow & purple flowers.","images":[{"src":"media/1996-ireland-glendalough-kilkenny-cashel-dingle-blaskets/A_0184_R_1.webp","w":900,"h":842,"caption":"Dingle Peninsula / Blaskets","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":17,"place_id":"camp-county-kerry-ireland","lon":-9.9087276,"lat":52.2208624,"place":"Camp, County Kerry, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Simon came out of the dunes to look at the lovely beach.","images":[]},{"seq":18,"place_id":"tralee-ireland","lon":-9.7057047,"lat":52.2692116,"place":"Tralee, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"main_stop","quote":"We spent a good 2 hours at the Tralee Aquadome, similar to Romsey Rapids, but with lovely steam room too.","images":[]},{"seq":19,"place_id":"killimer-shannon-car-ferry-ireland","lon":-9.3817629,"lat":52.6172284,"place":"Killimer (Shannon car ferry), Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"Elegant Victorian pier passed.","images":[]},{"seq":20,"place_id":"lahinch-county-clare-ireland","lon":-9.3459078,"lat":52.932149,"place":"Lahinch, County Clare, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"overnight_base","quote":"clean, bright, beer, Irish stew.","images":[{"src":"media/1996-ireland-glendalough-kilkenny-cashel-dingle-blaskets/A_0186_R_1.webp","w":675,"h":900,"caption":"Ireland August 1996 route map","type":"map"}]},{"seq":21,"place_id":"clonmacnoise-county-offaly-ireland","lon":-7.9857432,"lat":53.3263135,"place":"Clonmacnoise, County Offaly, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"main_stop","quote":"Cieran founded it with the help of Prince Diarmid, but Cieran died 7 months later of the Plague.","images":[]},{"seq":22,"place_id":"lough-ree-near-athlone-ireland","lon":-7.9885399,"lat":53.5593315,"place":"Lough Ree, near Athlone, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"overnight_base","quote":"We rowed through our section of the lake to another, while another, still bigger, lay beyond.","images":[{"src":"media/1996-ireland-glendalough-kilkenny-cashel-dingle-blaskets/A_0188_L_1.webp","w":510,"h":900,"caption":"Resurrection Panel, Figure More Ni Bhrien or figure of Wisdom on MacMahon Tomb; influenced by Nottingham alabaster carvings 1470 Ennis Friary","type":"sketch"},{"src":"media/1996-ireland-glendalough-kilkenny-cashel-dingle-blaskets/A_0188_R_1.webp","w":797,"h":900,"caption":"Clonmacnoice, Co Offaly Cross of the Scriptures","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":23,"place_id":"granard-county-longford-ireland","lon":-7.4910079,"lat":53.779362,"place":"Granard, County Longford, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"transit_stop","quote":"The friendly priest shook hands.","images":[]},{"seq":24,"place_id":"killyleagh-county-down-northern-ireland","lon":-5.6505384,"lat":54.3990651,"place":"Killyleagh, County Down, Northern Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Thomas & Peter played fire ball hockey at midnight on the tennis court","images":[]},{"seq":25,"place_id":"knowth-county-meath-ireland","lon":-6.4914013,"lat":53.7012036,"place":"Knowth, County Meath, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"main_stop","quote":"the Solstice was celebrated before even the pyramids.","images":[]},{"seq":26,"place_id":"dun-laoghaire-ireland","lon":-6.1360079,"lat":53.2922794,"place":"Dún Laoghaire, Ireland","date":"1996-08-03","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"It was a race down to Dun Laoghaire. Appalling signs through Dublin.","images":[]},{"seq":27,"place_id":"holyhead","lon":-4.631,"lat":53.309,"place":"Holyhead","date":"1996-08-03","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"We arrived with less than 15 min to spare, but it looks like the ferry will leave 40 min late, anyway.","images":[]},{"seq":28,"place_id":"meole-brace-shrewsbury-uk","lon":-2.